[[Category:Lists of county governors of Sweden|Stockholm]] [[Category:Stockholm-related lists|Governors of Stockholm County]] [[Category:Stockholm County]]

'''''Lockie's Topography of London, giving a concise local description of and accurate direction to every square, street, lane, court, dock, wharf, inn, public-office, &c. in the metropolis and its environs, including the new buildings to the present time, upon a plan never hitherto attempted. &c.''''' by John Lockie was an important [[gazetteer]] of [[London]] published in 1810.

The book was prepared by Lockie from his survey prepared for the insurers Phoenix Fire-Office of [[Lombard Street, London|Lombard Street]], for whom he was the Inspector of Buildings. It was printed by S. Couchman of [[Throgmorton Street]] and sold by a variety of booksellers in London who are listed on the title page. In the ''Preface'', Lockie commented that it had taken him seven years of "assiduity and patient labour" to prepare the contents and therefore he hoped that it would receive the patronage of the public. Lockie went on to add that "the whole Work having been accomplished by his own personal Exertions, he is enabled to offer the fullest Assurances of the Accuracy of its Execution."<ref>"Preface" in Lockie, John. (1810) ''Lockie's Topography of London''. Couchman: London.</ref>

The book was reprinted in facsimile form by the [[London Topographical Society]] in 1994.<ref>British Library catalogue search 13 June 2014.</ref>

